                                "text": "I don't get where  \"AST always leads to infinite-memory-assuming design\" implication is coming from.\n\nI can come up with counterexamples to many points in the article, eg. \"garbage collection comes from infinite memory thinking\", when to run java program you explicitly specify max allowed memory footprint with "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "-Xmx 1Gb",
                                "style": {
                                    "code": true
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": " .\nI guess 1 in 1000 of developers even heard term AST, and 1 out of 100 of those – had a hands on experience with \"it\".\nSo \"AST\" (whatever you actually mean by it) is not to blame for all the bloated crappy software in existence.\nWhy not blame Turing for a concept of infinite tape then? "
                            },
