        "client_msg_id": "1412035a-4935-479b-8e82-a958aa6a8c9d",
        "text": "Similar to how <https:\/\/www.drewlyton.com\/story\/the-future-is-not-self-hosted\/?utm_source=www.robertmao.com&amp;utm_medium=blog_link&amp;utm_campaign=default&amp;utm_content=www.drewlyton.com|self-hosting> doesn't seem like a viable path for getting off the cloud neither does the sound of self-scaffolding, as <@UC2A2ARPT> suggests he will undertake himself to get us off of slack. I'd love to see us have stronger values around community stewardship to take small steps towards the future we want, in some ways similar to communities like<https:\/\/mayfirst.coop\/en\/| May First Technology Movement> and <https:\/\/core.servus.at\/en\/toolbox\/servus-toolbox|servus>.",
