        "client_msg_id": "18B47B29-125D-42B8-9F2A-74328A36D70E",
        "text": "A communal project works well when the people are in the community so as to do that sort of communal work. But that's not why folks are here. It would be a different community, people who are willing to spend dozens or hundreds of volunteer hours building a thing and coordinating their efforts, who would do that project. The failure mode we've fallen into in the past is that there are lots of people who want to talk about it but zero (legit zero; not one) who want to make it.",
